---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Home"
  description="Malcolm Smith's story of surviving parental alienation — and a guide for parents walking the same path. Community, articles, and a free survival guide."
>

  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       1. HERO
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="hero-inner">
        <div class="hero-content">
          <p class="hero-eyebrow">For alienated parents</p>
          <h1 class="hero-heading">
            You haven't lost them.<br />
            <em>You've been pushed out.</em>
          </h1>
          <p class="hero-body">
            Parental alienation is one of the most painful experiences a parent can face —
            and one of the least understood. Malcolm Smith has lived it, survived it, and
            written the book on finding your way back to yourself and your child.
          </p>
          <div class="hero-actions">
            <a href="/free-guide" class="btn btn-primary">Get the Free Survival Guide</a>
            <a href="/the-book" class="btn btn-outline">About the Book</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-image-wrap">
          <div class="hero-image-placeholder" aria-hidden="true">
            <img
              src="/images/hero-path.jpg"
              alt="A path through a forest opening to light"
              width="560"
              height="630"
              loading="eager"
              decoding="async"
            />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       2. THE PROBLEM
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <p class="section-label">What is parental alienation?</p>
      <h2>When a child is turned against a loving parent</h2>
      <p class="lead">
        Parental alienation happens when one parent — through deliberate or unconscious
        behaviour — damages and destroys a child's relationship with the other parent.
        It is a form of psychological abuse that harms both child and parent.
      </p>
      <div class="problem-grid">
        <div class="problem-item">
          <div class="problem-icon" aria-hidden="true">◦</div>
          <p>Your child suddenly refuses all contact — with no explanation you can understand.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="problem-item">
          <div class="problem-icon" aria-hidden="true">◦</div>
          <p>They repeat things that sound like they've been coached — accusations, rejections, silence.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="problem-item">
          <div class="problem-icon" aria-hidden="true">◦</div>
          <p>Every legal and therapeutic avenue feels like it moves at a fraction of the pace the damage is done.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="problem-item">
          <div class="problem-icon" aria-hidden="true">◦</div>
          <p>The people around you don't understand why you can't just "fix it" or "move on."</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="problem-close">
        If any of this sounds familiar, you are not alone — and this community exists for you.
      </p>
      <a href="/you-are-not-alone" class="btn btn-outline" style="margin-top: 1rem;">See the data →</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       3. ABOUT THE AUTHOR
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="author-split">
        <div class="author-image-wrap">
          <img
            src="/images/malcolm-smith-author.jpg"
            alt="Malcolm Smith, author of Love Over Exile"
            width="420"
            height="500"
            loading="lazy"
            decoding="async"
            class="author-photo"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="author-content">
          <p class="section-label">About the author</p>
          <h2>Malcolm Smith</h2>
          <p>
            Malcolm Smith experienced parental alienation first-hand — the confusion,
            the grief, the legal maze, and the long, slow work of rebuilding himself
            while holding on to love for his children.
          </p>
          <p>
            <em>Love Over Exile</em> is not a clinical manual. It is the account of a
            father who refused to disappear — and what he learned about surviving,
            staying present, and choosing love over bitterness when everything pushed
            him toward exile.
          </p>
          <blockquote class="pull-quote">
            "I didn't write this book because I had all the answers.
            I wrote it because I needed it to exist — and it didn't."
          </blockquote>
          <a href="/about" class="btn btn-outline" style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Read Malcolm's story →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       4. THE BOOK
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="section section-dark">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="book-split">
        <div class="book-cover-wrap">
          <div class="book-cover-placeholder">
            <img
              src="/images/book-cover.jpg"
              alt="Love Over Exile book cover"
              width="340"
              height="460"
              loading="lazy"
              decoding="async"
            />
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="book-content">
          <p class="section-label-light">The book</p>
          <h2>Love Over Exile</h2>
          <p>
            A book for alienated parents — not about the law, not about the other
            parent, but about <em>you</em>: how to survive, how to stay whole, and how
            to remain a source of love even when you cannot be present.
          </p>
          <ul class="book-parts">
            <li>
              <span class="part-number">Part I</span>
              <span class="part-title">Understanding Parental Alienation</span>
              <span class="part-desc">What it is, how it works, and why it happens</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="part-number">Part II</span>
              <span class="part-title">The Survival Guide</span>
              <span class="part-desc">Practical strategies for the acute phase</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="part-number">Part III</span>
              <span class="part-title">Inner Freedom</span>
              <span class="part-desc">Finding peace, purpose, and yourself again</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <div class="book-actions">
            <a href="/the-book" class="btn btn-primary">Join the Waitlist</a>
            <a href="/the-book" class="btn btn-outline-light" style="font-size:0.88rem;">Learn more →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       5. THREE JOURNEYS
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <p class="section-label">Three journeys</p>
        <h2>Where do you want to start?</h2>
        <p class="section-intro">
          The site mirrors the book's three-part structure. Wherever you are in your
          experience, there is a path for you.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="journeys-grid">
        <a href="/understanding" class="journey-card card">
          <div class="journey-number" aria-hidden="true">I</div>
          <h3>Understanding<br />Parental Alienation</h3>
          <p>
            What is happening, why it happens, and how to recognise the patterns.
            Evidence-based, compassionate, and honest.
          </p>
          <span class="journey-link">Start here →</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/survival-guide" class="journey-card card">
          <div class="journey-number" aria-hidden="true">II</div>
          <h3>The<br />Survival Guide</h3>
          <p>
            Practical, actionable strategies for the acute phase: legal options,
            communication tactics, and protecting your mental health.
          </p>
          <span class="journey-link">Read more →</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/inner-freedom" class="journey-card card">
          <div class="journey-number" aria-hidden="true">III</div>
          <h3>Inner<br />Freedom</h3>
          <p>
            Finding peace, rebuilding your identity, and choosing love over exile —
            even while the situation remains unresolved.
          </p>
          <span class="journey-link">Explore →</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       6. YOU ARE NOT ALONE
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="section section-dark">
    <div class="container-narrow" style="text-align:center;">
      <p class="section-label-light">The scale of this</p>
      <h2>You Are Not Alone</h2>
      <div class="stats-row">
        <div class="stat-item">
          <span class="stat-number">22M</span>
          <span class="stat-label">children worldwide affected by parental alienation</span>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-divider" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <div class="stat-item">
          <span class="stat-number">1 in 5</span>
          <span class="stat-label">divorced families report significant alienating behaviours</span>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-divider" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <div class="stat-item">
          <span class="stat-number">0</span>
          <span class="stat-label">mainstream resources combine lived experience, community, and healing</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p style="opacity:0.75; margin-bottom:2rem;">
        The research confirms what you already know in your bones. What most resources
        miss is the human side — which is exactly why this community exists.
      </p>
      <a href="/you-are-not-alone" class="btn btn-outline-light">Read the research →</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       7. FROM THE ARTICLES
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <p class="section-label">Latest writing</p>
        <h2>From the Articles</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="articles-grid">
        <article class="article-card card">
          <div class="article-meta">
            <span class="article-tag">Understanding PA</span>
            <span class="article-date">Coming soon</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="article-title">Signs of Parental Alienation: What to Look For and What It Means</h3>
          <p class="article-excerpt">
            The patterns that indicate deliberate alienation versus normal post-separation conflict —
            and why distinguishing them matters for your strategy.
          </p>
          <a href="/articles" class="article-link">Read more →</a>
        </article>
        <article class="article-card card">
          <div class="article-meta">
            <span class="article-tag">Survival Guide</span>
            <span class="article-date">Coming soon</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="article-title">How to Cope With Parental Alienation: A Framework for the Acute Phase</h3>
          <p class="article-excerpt">
            When you're in the middle of it, the world feels like it's collapsing.
            Here is a structure that has helped parents survive the worst periods.
          </p>
          <a href="/articles" class="article-link">Read more →</a>
        </article>
        <article class="article-card card">
          <div class="article-meta">
            <span class="article-tag">Inner Freedom</span>
            <span class="article-date">Coming soon</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="article-title">Choosing Love Over Exile: What It Actually Means to Stay Present</h3>
          <p class="article-excerpt">
            "Staying present" sounds like a platitude until you understand what it requires
            — and what it gives back.
          </p>
          <a href="/articles" class="article-link">Read more →</a>
        </article>
      </div>
      <div style="text-align:center; margin-top:2.5rem;">
        <a href="/articles" class="btn btn-outline">All articles →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       8. COMMUNITY
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="community-split">
        <div class="community-content">
          <p class="section-label">The community</p>
          <h2>A place for people who understand</h2>
          <p>
            Because they've lived it too. The Love Over Exile community is a moderated
            forum for alienated parents — not a social media group with no memory, not
            a helpline you can't reach, but a real place where experience is shared
            and honoured.
          </p>
          <ul class="community-features">
            <li>Moderated by Malcolm and AI — real attention, real safety</li>
            <li>Categories for legal experiences, emotional wellbeing, survival strategies, and success stories</li>
            <li>A crisis protocol that means you're never left alone in a dark moment</li>
            <li>Fully free to join</li>
          </ul>
          <a href="/community" class="btn btn-primary" style="margin-top:1.5rem;">Join the Community</a>
        </div>
        <div class="community-image-wrap">
          <img
            src="/images/community-warmth.jpg"
            alt="Warm candlelight — a symbol of connection"
            width="480"
            height="420"
            loading="lazy"
            decoding="async"
            class="community-image"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       9. FREE GUIDE CTA
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="section free-guide-cta">
    <div class="container-narrow" style="text-align:center;">
      <p class="section-label">Free resource</p>
      <h2>Start with the Free Survival Guide</h2>
      <p class="lead" style="max-width:600px; margin-inline:auto;">
        A concise, practical guide for parents in the acute phase of parental alienation.
        What to do, what not to do, and how to hold yourself together.
        Free — in exchange for joining the community.
      </p>
      <a href="/free-guide" class="btn btn-primary" style="font-size:1.05rem; padding:1rem 2.4rem;">
        Get the Free Survival Guide →
      </a>
      <p class="guide-note">No spam. Unsubscribe at any time.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
/* ── Hero ─────────────────────────────────────── */
.hero {
  padding-block: 5rem 4rem;
  overflow: hidden;
}
.hero-inner {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
  gap: 4rem;
  align-items: center;
}
.hero-eyebrow {
  font-size: 0.8rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--color-amber);
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}
.hero-heading { margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }
.hero-body {
  font-size: 1.1rem;
  line-height: 1.7;
  color: var(--color-charcoal-mid);
  margin-bottom: 2rem;
  max-width: 500px;
}
.hero-actions { display: flex; gap: 1rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }
.hero-image-wrap { position: relative; }
.hero-image-placeholder {
  border-radius: 16px;
  overflow: hidden;
  aspect-ratio: 9/11;
  background: var(--color-border);
}
.hero-image-placeholder img { width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; }

/* ── Section chrome ───────────────────────────── */
.section-label {
  font-size: 0.78rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--color-amber);
  margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
}
.section-label-light {
  font-size: 0.78rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--color-amber-light);
  margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
}
.section-header { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 3rem; }
.section-intro {
  font-size: 1.05rem;
  color: var(--color-charcoal-mid);
  max-width: 560px;
  margin-inline: auto;
  margin-top: 0.75rem;
}
.lead {
  font-size: 1.1rem;
  line-height: 1.75;
  color: var(--color-charcoal-mid);
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
}

/* ── The Problem ──────────────────────────────── */
.problem-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
  gap: 1rem;
  margin: 2rem 0;
}
.problem-item {
  display: flex;
  gap: 0.75rem;
  align-items: flex-start;
  padding: 1.25rem;
  background: var(--color-ivory);
  border-radius: 10px;
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
}
.problem-icon {
  font-size: 1.4rem;
  color: var(--color-amber);
  flex-shrink: 0;
  line-height: 1;
  margin-top: 0.1em;
}
.problem-item p { font-size: 0.95rem; margin: 0; line-height: 1.6; }
.problem-close {
  font-style: italic;
  color: var(--color-charcoal-mid);
  border-left: 3px solid var(--color-amber);
  padding-left: 1rem;
  margin: 0;
}

/* ── About the Author ─────────────────────────── */
.author-split {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 420px 1fr;
  gap: 4rem;
  align-items: center;
}
.author-photo {
  width: 100%;
  border-radius: 16px;
  object-fit: cover;
  aspect-ratio: 4/5;
  background: var(--color-border);
}

/* ── The Book ─────────────────────────────────── */
.book-split {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 340px 1fr;
  gap: 4rem;
  align-items: center;
}
.book-cover-placeholder {
  border-radius: 12px;
  overflow: hidden;
  box-shadow: 0 24px 60px rgba(0,0,0,0.4);
  aspect-ratio: 3/4;
  background: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
}
.book-cover-placeholder img { width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; }
.book-parts {
  list-style: none;
  padding: 0;
  margin: 1.5rem 0 2rem;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 0.75rem;
}
.book-parts li {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 60px 1fr;
  grid-template-rows: auto auto;
  column-gap: 1rem;
  padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
  background: rgba(255,255,255,0.06);
  border-radius: 8px;
  border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
}
.part-number {
  font-size: 0.72rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--color-amber-light);
  grid-row: 1;
  grid-column: 1;
  align-self: center;
}
.part-title {
  font-weight: 600;
  color: var(--color-ivory);
  grid-row: 1;
  grid-column: 2;
  font-size: 0.95rem;
}
.part-desc {
  font-size: 0.82rem;
  color: rgba(247,243,238,0.6);
  grid-row: 2;
  grid-column: 2;
  margin-top: 0.15rem;
}
.book-actions { display: flex; gap: 1rem; align-items: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }

/* ── Three Journeys ───────────────────────────── */
.journeys-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
  gap: 1.5rem;
}
.journey-card {
  text-decoration: none;
  color: inherit;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
}
.journey-number {
  font-family: var(--font-serif);
  font-size: 2rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  color: var(--color-amber);
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
  opacity: 0.7;
}
.journey-card h3 { font-size: 1.2rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; line-height: 1.25; }
.journey-card p {
  font-size: 0.92rem;
  color: var(--color-charcoal-mid);
  line-height: 1.65;
  flex: 1;
  margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
}
.journey-link {
  font-size: 0.88rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  color: var(--color-amber);
  transition: color 0.15s;
}
.journey-card:hover .journey-link { color: var(--color-green-deep); }

/* ── Stats ────────────────────────────────────── */
.stats-row {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
  align-items: flex-start;
  gap: 2rem;
  margin: 2.5rem 0 2rem;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
}
.stat-item {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 0.5rem;
  max-width: 180px;
  text-align: center;
}
.stat-number {
  font-family: var(--font-serif);
  font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--color-amber-light);
  line-height: 1;
}
.stat-label {
  font-size: 0.85rem;
  color: rgba(247,243,238,0.7);
  line-height: 1.5;
}
.stat-divider {
  width: 1px;
  height: 60px;
  background: rgba(247,243,238,0.15);
  align-self: center;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

/* ── Articles ─────────────────────────────────── */
.articles-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
  gap: 1.5rem;
}
.article-card { display: flex; flex-direction: column; }
.article-meta {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  align-items: center;
  margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
}
.article-tag {
  font-size: 0.72rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--color-amber);
  background: rgba(196,154,60,0.1);
  border-radius: 4px;
  padding: 0.2em 0.6em;
}
.article-date { font-size: 0.78rem; color: var(--color-warm-grey); }
.article-title { font-size: 1.05rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; flex: 1; }
.article-excerpt {
  font-size: 0.9rem;
  color: var(--color-charcoal-mid);
  line-height: 1.65;
  margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
}
.article-link {
  font-size: 0.88rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  color: var(--color-amber);
  text-decoration: none;
  margin-top: auto;
  transition: color 0.15s;
}
.article-link:hover { color: var(--color-green-deep); }

/* ── Community ────────────────────────────────── */
.community-split {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 480px;
  gap: 4rem;
  align-items: center;
}
.community-features {
  list-style: none;
  padding: 0;
  margin: 1.25rem 0 0;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 0.6rem;
}
.community-features li {
  padding-left: 1.4rem;
  position: relative;
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  line-height: 1.6;
}
.community-features li::before {
  content: '✓';
  position: absolute;
  left: 0;
  color: var(--color-amber);
  font-weight: 700;
}
.community-image {
  width: 100%;
  border-radius: 16px;
  object-fit: cover;
  aspect-ratio: 8/7;
  background: var(--color-border);
}

/* ── Free Guide CTA ───────────────────────────── */
.free-guide-cta {
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-ivory-alt) 0%, rgba(196,154,60,0.06) 100%);
  border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
}
.guide-note {
  font-size: 0.8rem;
  color: var(--color-warm-grey);
  margin-top: 1rem;
  margin-bottom: 0;
}

/* ── Responsive ───────────────────────────────── */
@media (max-width: 1024px) {
  .hero-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 3rem; }
  .hero-image-wrap { display: none; }
  .author-split { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .author-image-wrap { display: none; }
  .book-split { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .book-cover-wrap { display: none; }
  .community-split { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .community-image-wrap { display: none; }
}
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .problem-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .journeys-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .articles-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
